{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870455087,"sessionID":"ses_285df9baeffeV4Cu7d2awKyVVg","part":{"id":"prt_d7a20a900001gKrnk2uMdaFxdz","messageID":"msg_d7a20a0b3001UGxR2kvU7FGGr1","sessionID":"ses_285df9baeffeV4Cu7d2awKyVVg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b55342c05a714ebe8e2cf07c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n11: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n12: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n13: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n14: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n15: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n16: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n17: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n18: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n19: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n20: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n21: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n22: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n23: \n24: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n25: \n26: ```python\n27: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n28: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n29: \n30: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n31: ```\n32: \n33: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: __all__ = [\n37:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n38:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n39:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n40: ]\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n44: \n45: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n46: \n47: | Component | Resolved settings |\n48: |-----------|-------------------|\n49: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n50: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n51: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n52: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n53: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n54: \n55: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n59:     def __init__(\n60:         self,\n61:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n62:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n63:         ttl: int = 3600,\n64:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n65:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n66:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n67:         verbose: bool = False,\n68:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n69:     ): ...\n70: \n71:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n72: \n73:     def __enter__(self): ...\n74:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n75: \n76:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n77: \n78:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n79:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n80:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n81:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n82:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n83:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n84: ```\n85: \n86: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n87: \n88: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n89: \n90: ```python\n91: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n92:     def __init__(\n93:         self,\n94:         agent_name: str,\n95:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n96:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n97:         verbose: bool = False,\n98:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n99:         timeout: int = 120,\n100:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n101:     ): ...\n102: \n103:     def __enter__(self): ...\n104:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n105: \n106:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n107: \n108:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n112: \n113: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n114: \n115: ```python\n116: class ControlPlaneClient:\n117:     def __init__(\n118:         self,\n119:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n120:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n121:         timeout: int = 120,\n122:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n123:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n124:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n125:     ): ...\n126: \n127:     def create_session(\n128:         self,\n129:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n130:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n131:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n132:         ttl: int = 3600,\n133:     ) -> str: ...\n134: \n135:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n136: \n137:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ### Control plane — HTTP\n141: \n142: | Method | Path | Notes |\n143: |--------|------|-------|\n144: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n145: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n146: \n147: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n148: \n149: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n150: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n151: \n152: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n153: \n154: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n155: \n156: ```python\n157: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n158:     def __init__(\n159:         self,\n160:         session_id: str,\n161:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n162:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n163:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n164:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n165:         timeout: int = 120,\n166:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n167:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n168:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n169:     ): ...\n170: \n171:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n172: \n173:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n174:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n175:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n176:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n177:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n178:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n179:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n183: \n184: If `base_url` is not provided:\n185: \n186: ```text\n187: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n188: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n192: \n193: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n194: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n195: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n196: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n197: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n198: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n199: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n200: \n201: **Headers:**\n202: \n203: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n204: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n205: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n206: \n207: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n208: \n209: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n213:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n214: \n215:     def __init__(\n216:         self,\n217:         router_url: str,\n218:         namespace: str,\n219:         agent_name: str,\n220:         timeout: int = 120,\n221:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n222:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n223:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n224:     ): ...\n225: \n226:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n227: \n228:     def invoke(\n229:         self,\n230:         session_id: str,\n231:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n232:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n233:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n234: \n235:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n239: \n240: ```text\n241: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n242: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ### Data plane — HTTP\n246: \n247: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n248: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n249: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n250: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n251: \n252: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n253: \n254: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: def create_session(\n258:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n259:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n260: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n261: ```\n262: \n263: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n264: \n265: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n266: \n267: ```python\n268: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n272: \n273: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n280: \n281: ```python\n282: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n283:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n284:     pass\n285: \n286: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n287:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n288:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n289:         self.stderr = stderr\n290:         self.command = command\n291:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n292: \n293: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n294:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n295:     pass\n296: \n297: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n298:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n299:     pass\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n303: \n304: ```toml\n305: dependencies = [\n306:     \"requests\",\n307:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n308:     \"cryptography\",\n309: ]\n310: ```\n311: \n312: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n313: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n314: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n319: \n320: ## Purpose\n321: \n322: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n323: \n324: ## Requirements\n325: \n326: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n327: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n330: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n331: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n332: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n335: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n336: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n337: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n340: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n341: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n342: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n345: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n348: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n349: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n350: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n351: \n352: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n353: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n354: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n355: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n356: \n357: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n358: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Context manager\n361: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n362: - **WHEN** the block exits\n363: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n366: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n367: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n368: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n371: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n372: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n373: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n376: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Create session\n379: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n380: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n381: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: Delete session\n384: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n385: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n386: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n389: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n390: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n391: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n392: \n393: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n394: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Execute command\n397: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n398: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: Files API\n401: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n403: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n404: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n405: \n406: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n407: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n410: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n411: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n412: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n413: \n414: ### Requirement: Session header management\n415: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n418: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n419: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n420: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n423: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Command failure\n426: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n427: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n428: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n431: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n432: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n433: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n434: \n435: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n436: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n439: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n440: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n441: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n444: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n445: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n446: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n447: \n448: ---\n449: \n450: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: Previous proposal:\n455: [Stage ST-1 completed]\n456: \n457: Include: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy.\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Package layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775870455066,"end":1775870455084}}}}
